        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Bulgaria)/8–645:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-21T20:00:00-04:00">August 21, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>268. On basis Berlin agreement Dept. agrees adoption clearance procedure
                    suggested urtel 422, Aug. 6 at least 7 days advance notice of arrival and
                    identity etc. of official personnel to be given in each case, and you may so
                    inform Gen. Crane. However, we prefer that pending final agreement on revised
                    statutes for operation of ACC Gen. Crane not formally advise Gen. Biryusov of
                    intention to adopt this procedure unless he believes there is compelling reason
                    to do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
